<h3>Troubleshooting - experiencing problems using a messageboard?</h3>


<a name="post"> </a><h4>I can't post my message</h4>

<p>Check the following things first:</p><br>

<p>Have you created a BBC membership?  You need to create a membership before you can post a message on the messageboards. The process is fast and painless, but we will need your email address.  Your email address will never appear on the site and we won't publish it or give it to anybody. It will however, be used as a point of contact with you if the moderators ever need to contact you about one of your messages.</p><br>

<p>If you have joined, did you log in?  You can do that from the top of any page on the messageboard.</p><br>

<p>Is the messageboard 'open'?  Some of the messageboards have opening times, which mean that you won't be able to post when it's closed.</p><br>

<a href="#top" class="top">&lt;&lt; Back to top</a>



<a name="removed"> </a><h4>My message appears to have been removed</h4>
<ul>
<li>If your message was removed by a moderator because it broke one of the House Rules, you should have received an email informing you of this.</li>

<li>The messageboard is sometimes quite busy, and as a result, messages can take some time to appear.      </li>

<li>It's also possible there's a technical fault with the board, but if this is the case, messages are usually reinstated.</li>
</ul>
